[lyottia_conversation_13_party_leader_first]
{
	[text*]
	{
		screen_text = "Which of the gods of luck guided you here traveler? Do you realize how lucky you are to be alive if you've traveled from that direction? You killed the necromancer? That must have been very tough fight. We were considering to attack it, but outcome was unsure, and should we have failed, the villagers would have been left to die alone in these disgusting lands. We have been able to push throught the undead hordes, but the lithids got us cornered in the caverns. You must have seen our blockade. We spent about a day fending off lithids who managed to slip beneath the blockade. The we heard fighting, so we took the opportunity to move out of the caverns. Lizzith urged us to encamp, however. She senses that five powerful lithid necromancers are residing in nearby caverns. She does not think it is safe to move until we have killed them. We've had hard time figuring out how to split our forces, so that camp remains safe and we still have enough power to vanquish the lithids. Now that you're here, how about you deal with the lithids while we defend the camp? You should be able to find them in caves nearby, there should be five of them. You are surely headed in the same direction, and as slayer of necromancer, you should not have trouble dealing with them.";
	  f scroll_rate = 10.000000;
	}
}
[lyottia_conversation_13_party_leader_next]
{
	[text*]
	{
		screen_text = "Lizzith will observe your battle against the lithids with her magical senses. Once they're dead, we'll move out. You'll surely catch up with us, we won't move too fast in this dangerous place. There is no point going back. The necromancer may be dead, but the place is rotten forever. Villagers would find nothing but death there anyway. Villages further back are struggling on their own with the blockade going on, they would not be able to feed the refugees. The only reasonable thing to do is to push further.";
	  f scroll_rate = 10.000000;
	}
}
